commit.message:
Pass reader error messages along (#28)

This fixes problems like the one mentioned in issue #27 where using the
reader in Python 2.x with it's default `str` type would throw an error,
but the error message was overridden. There was a similar change made
for issue #5.

I don't believe a new test is required for this since
https://github.com/ryanhiebert/backports.csv/blob/1.0.5/tests.py#L853-L856
covers the source exception and this is more about the messaging
bubbling up. It would be possible if needed to check the message higher
up the chain though.

Testing cleanups (#29)

Python 3.3 doesn't build, because tox no longer supports it. To
get around this, we need to use pytest directly for Python 3.3.

Tox-Travis has deprecated the "after all" feature, in favor of
Travis build stages, which are in general a better solution to
the problem addressed. So this also converts to using them.
